Matlab nums[0] aur nums[1] ka sum 9 hai, jo target se match karta hai.

Summary (In Simple Terms):
1ï¸âƒ£ Ek hashmap banate hain jo numbers ka index store karta hai.
2ï¸âƒ£ Loop chalate hain:

Har number ke liye remain = target - num nikalte hain.

Agar remain hashmap me hai, to uska index return kar dete hain.

Nahi hai to current number ko hashmap me daal dete hain.
3ï¸âƒ£ Jab match milta hai, to indices return ho jate hain.

Dry Run (For Another Example)
Agar nums = [3, 2, 4] aur target = 6 ho, to steps kuch aise honge:

makefile
Copy
Edit
hashmap = {}

i = 0, num = 3  â†’ remain = 6 - 3 = 3  â†’ hashmap = {3: 0}
i = 1, num = 2  â†’ remain = 6 - 2 = 4  â†’ hashmap = {3: 0, 2: 1}
i = 2, num = 4  â†’ remain = 6 - 4 = 2  âœ… 2 hashmap me mila at index 1  
Return: [1, 2]
Output: [1, 2]

Time Complexity:
O(n) because each number ko sirf ek baar check kar rahe hain.

Hashmap me lookup O(1) hota hai.

Key Takeaways:
âœ… Fastest approach (HashMap use karne se)
âœ… Space Complexity: O(n) (Kyunki hashmap extra space use karta hai)
âœ… Loop ek hi baar chalta hai, isliye efficient hai!

